# Lean Apply Checklist

Read when: applying or migrating `templates-lean` into a project.
Skip when: already applied and validated.

## 1) Apply Files
- [ ] `AI_AGENT.md.template` copied to `AI_AGENT.md`
- [ ] `SESSION_BRIEF.md.template` copied to `docs/SESSION_BRIEF.md`
- [ ] `CONTEXT_ROUTING.md.template` copied to `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md`
- [ ] `PROJECT_CANVAS.md.template` copied to `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md`
- [ ] `ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md.template` copied to `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md`
- [ ] `TECH_STACK.md.template` copied to `docs/TECH_STACK.md`
- [ ] `OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md.template` copied to `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md`
- [ ] `MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md.template` copied to `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` if Tier B/C
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md.template` copied to `CHANGELOG.md`
- [ ] `MIGRATION_GUIDE.md.template` copied to `docs/MIGRATION_GUIDE.md`
- [ ] `TEMPLATE_INDEX.yaml.template` copied to `docs/TEMPLATE_INDEX.yaml`

## 2) Required Setup Work
- [ ] Set the selected tier
- [ ] Fill verify and AI context commands
- [ ] Fill current session brief
- [ ] Fill current project canvas
- [ ] Update startup prompt to point only to `AI_AGENT.md`

## 3) Migration-Specific Work
- [ ] If migrating from `templates-v2`, remove full-doc default startup behavior
- [ ] If migrating from no template, map existing commands and workflows into lean docs
- [ ] Keep traceability and audit docs for Tier B/C projects

## 4) Final Validation
- [ ] A routine task can start with only the three startup docs
- [ ] Verify gate command is defined
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` contains `Unreleased`
- [ ] Tier B/C projects have traceability coverage in place